## Conclusion

Research is indispensable in making nursing practice safe. It provides the scientific basis for identifying, validating, and implementing best practices that improve patient outcomes and reduce harm. The integration of evidence-based practice, supported by translational research and implementation science, ensures that nursing care is current, effective, and tailored to patient needs. Despite challenges in translating research into practice, ongoing advancements in nursing research and education, coupled with organizational support, are crucial for sustaining safe nursing practices. Nurses’ engagement in research not only enhances their professional competence but also fosters a culture of safety that benefits patients and healthcare systems alike.

